headline: ScaleReady Announces Award of a G-Rex速 Grant to the Gates Institute's Translational Sciences Laboratory
summary: ScaleReady, in collaboration with Wilson Wolf Manufacturing, Bio-Techne Corporation and CellReady, today announced that the Translational Sciences Laboratory at Gates Institute, a leading contract development and manufacturing organization (CDMO) based at the University of Colorado Anschutz Medical Campus, has been awarded a $300,000 G-Rex速 Grant to develop a modular G-Rex centric CAR T-cell manufacturing platform.
